rComments: I applied to the translation program because of this class. Bella's slides are hilarious, she's funny and quirky and wanted our feedback. She was upfront about this being her first time teaching and seemed to care a lot about the work we were doing for class. Do your homework because she'll call on you but at least doesn't make you feel bad.

Awesome class. Bella's an interesting character. Genuinely funny. Teaching method is engaging. How to write resumescover lettersmemosagendas, etc: that's basically the entirety of the course. 2 assignments and one exam, not too bad considering it's a simple course. I only wish she would've made clear the criteria for her assignments.

At first she comes off funny and quirky, but after a while it can get a bit annoying and unprofessional. Tries to be funny in slides, gets old really quickly. Posts all her lectures online. Wastes the last 30 minutes of class sometimes. Only 2 assignments and 1 midterm. Pretty hard grader, not a really hard class though.
